In case of $\text{r}_1$, we will have:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{FV}_1&=\text{C} \times \frac{\left(1+1\right)^2-1}{1}\\
&=\text{C} \times \frac{4-1}{1}\\
&=3 \times \text{C}
\end{aligned}$$

In case of $\text{r}_1$, we will have:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{PV}_1&=\text{C} \times \frac{1-\left(\dfrac{1}{1+1}\right)^2}{1}\\
&=\text{C} \times (1-0.25)\\
&=0.75 \times \text{C}
\end{aligned}$$
